Responsible for TPM implementation at the Supply Chain Operations at the Eastern Europe and Central Asia Cluster. 
The main activities are:
- Audit and coach the two converting factories situated in Moscow and Kiev aiming to implement the culture of continuous improvement;
- Support the EE&amp;CA converting factories to develop their local strategies aiming to reach the global and cluster objectives through a sustainable process improvements.  
- Develop local TPM coordinators and managers thorugh continuous coaching and support related to the continuous improvement process;
- Support the implementation of the continuous improvement program at the order management, logisitics and planning process;
- Support the factories at the certification process conducted by the Japanese Institute of Plant Management.

Responsible to coordinate the continuous improvement process at the NEAO Cluster including three plants located in Fairfield,Sydney - Australia, Yoju - Korea and Gotemba - Japan. Main responsibilities and challenges were:
- Support and drive continuous improvement process in factories being closed like the converting factories in Yoju and Sydney;
- Support other asian factories including factories located in Singapore, India and China;
- Understand Japanese TPM implementation process in Gotemba and adapt to the global WCM way respeciting culture differences and promoting best practices wordwide;
- Seek and promote the benchmarking and cross-fertilization culture in Japan; 
- Coordinate Japanese TPM consultants ensuring alignment to global WCM processes;
